## Architecture (always)

```
Sources (registry) â†’ Ingest â†’ Normalize â†’ Store â†’ API routes â†’ Mobile/Web client â†’ Open original URL
```

| Module | Path | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Source registry | `api/src/sources/registry.js` | Allowlisted feeds; enable/disable; ingest method |
| Ingest | `api/src/ingest/feeds.js`, `scrape.js` | Pull RSS/Atom/scrape (metadata only) |
| Normalize | `api/src/normalize/news-item.js` | `NewsItem` shape, excerpt cap, dedupe keys |
| Store | `api/src/store/` | Cache (memory â†’ DB later) |
| Routes | `api/src/index.js` | HTTP only â€” no ingest logic inline |
| Mobile API client | `mobile/src/services/` | Fetch JSON â€” no RSS, no UI |
| Screens | `mobile/App.js` or `mobile/src/screens/` | UI only â€” calls API client |

**Ethics (every phase):** title + short excerpt (â‰¤300 chars) + canonical URL + attribution. Tap opens original in browser. Never republish full article body in-app.

**Four ingest paths (expand in Phase 3):** (1) RSS/Atom, (2) scrape API fallback, (3) curated registry, (4) third-party aggregator feeds.

