## Phase 1 â€” Core feed (official sources)

**Vertical slice:** User sees Cursor changelog + GitHub releases on device; tap opens original.

**Sources (registry, enabled):**
- `https://cursor.com/rss.xml` (changelog)
- `https://github.com/getcursor/cursor/releases.atom`

**API:** `GET /v1/news`, `GET /v1/sources`, `POST /v1/ingest`, `GET /v1/status`, `GET /health`

**Mobile:** Feed list, refresh (ingest + reload), disclaimer banner, open link via `Linking.openURL`.

**Done when:** Refresh returns real items; every card opens a valid external URL; disclaimer visible.

**Do not:** scraping, aggregators, payments, push, UI polish.

---

## Phase 2 â€” Dedupe + registry quality

**Vertical slice:** One clean timeline â€” duplicate stories appear once.

**Work:** `dedupeNewsItems` by canonical URL; official source wins over aggregator when added later. Sort by `publishedAt` desc. Expose source metadata on `GET /v1/sources`.

**Done when:** Same story from two sources shows once; registry is the single place to add sources.

**Do not:** change mobile UI layout beyond what dedupe requires.

---

## Phase 3 â€” Expand coverage (four ingest paths)

**Vertical slice:** More Cursor news sources, same rules.

**Add incrementally (one source at a time, test each):**
1. RSS/Atom â€” forum/community feeds if available
2. Scrape â€” `scrape.js` behind env flag; metadata only; robots/ToS respect
3. Registry â€” new rows in `registry.js` (later DB)
4. Aggregators â€” e.g. Releasebot Cursor RSS (`enabled: false` until verified)

**Done when:** â‰¥2 ingest methods live; each source documented in registry with `ingestMethod`, `attributionLabel`, `maxExcerptChars`.

**Do not:** full-page scrape storage; paywalled content republishing.

---

## Phase 4 â€” UX essentials (functional, not beautiful)

**Vertical slice:** Daily-usable reader on Windows + phone.

**Work:** loading/error states; category filter (All, Changelog, Releases, Blog, Forum); About panel (unofficial notice, how sources work); empty state; API-down hint with dev commands.

**Done when:** User can filter, refresh, and understand unofficial status without confusion.

**Do not:** animations, custom themes, marketing polish.

---

## Phase 5 â€” Notifications

**Vertical slice:** User gets alerted when **new** items appear (opt-in).

**Work:** scheduled ingest job (`api/src/jobs/`); diff new vs last run; device token registration endpoint; Expo push or web push (PWA path via `web/` if needed). Per-category toggles: Changelog, Releases, Blog. Default digest; instant = Pro later (Phase 6).

**Done when:** New changelog entry triggers notification user subscribed to; mute/opt-out works.

**Do not:** spam; notify on duplicates; push unrelated marketing.

---

## Phase 6 â€” Membership ($1â€“$5/mo)

**Vertical slice:** Optional support â€” **core news stays free.**

| Tier | Price | Free | Paid |
